[Patient] Can you recommend exercises for my heart failure? 
[Healthcare Educator] Walking, swimming, or light weight training are good options for you. 
[Patient] How often should I exercise? 
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for at least 30 minutes of exercise most days of the week. 
[Patient] Is it safe for me to exercise at my age? 
[Healthcare Educator] Yes, as long as you start slowly and listen to your body. 
[Patient] Are there any specific exercises I should avoid? 
[Healthcare Educator] Avoid high-intensity activities and heavy lifting that may strain your heart.